news.title: Andhra Pradesh to digitise 15 crore land registration documents since 1850
news.para: Over 50 per cent of the office buildings are either located at private premises or in dilapidated structures. Since land records are very crucial for handling registration deeds, the government has decided to go for complete digitisation.

news.title: PMRDA lists violation of law at 62 sites in five talukas
news.para: The registration department has taken action against 44 of their officers for illegally registering 10,561 documents violating the Real Estate Regulatory Authority Act and Maharashtra Prevention of Fragmentation and Consolidation of Holdings Act.

news.title: South Delhi civic body collects Rs 1,081 crore in property tax in 2021-22
news.para: In a statement, the corporation said that it achieved a record-breaking figure of Rs 1,081 crore in 2021-22. In the previous year, it was Rs 943 crore.

news.title: About 100 villages in Gurugram now declared Lal Dora-free
news.para: Lal Dora means red thread. Lal Dora land refers to population land that does not fall under the purview of the civic bodies, meaning their ownership depends on the one who literally possesses the same.

news.title: Property tax payments made easy with QR codes in Chennai
news.para: Residents will be able to pay taxes, renew trade licenses and get status on building approvals on WhatsApp. The Namma Chennaiapp which has more than 1. 2 lakh subscribers will be improved further adding more services to it.

news.title: DTCP asks NBCC to take call on refund to Green View buyers in a month
news.para: The DTCP’s direction was conveyed to officials of the state-owned construction firm by DTP (enforcement) RS Batth at a meeting on Friday, in which many other issues concerning the Green View residents were discussed.

news.title: Chandigarh: 15 associations to jointly oppose building misuse penalty
news.para: During the meeting, which was held in Industrial Area, Phase 2, it was decided that all associations would submit their suggestions and objections on the public notice separately after consultations with their legal teams.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board starts issuing eviction notices
news.para: The list of defaulters includes owners of small flats given under slum rehabilitation schemes, commercial and residential flats in different sectors and colonies, and slum dwellers given houses under affordable rental housing schemes (ARHC).

news.title: Chandigarh: Over 4,000 pay Rs 1.4 crore property tax in a week
news.para: Most of the revenue has come from residential property — Rs 1.03 crore from 4,161 taxpayers — as compared to Rs 39 lakh from 546 owners of commercial properties.

news.title: All group housing societies to be checked for fire safety standards
news.para: ​On April 7 night, fire broke out in a flat on the fourth floor of Annapurna Grandeur apartment under the limits of Sigra police station area. Later, the fire engulfed two neighbouring flats.

news.title: Pune collector to check of over 10,000 illegal documents
news.para: The registration department has taken action against 44 of their officers for illegally registering 10,561 documents violating the Real Estate Regulatory Authority Act and Maharashtra Prevention of Fragmentation and Consolidation of Holdings Act.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC hears PIL on illegal use of stone crushers
news.para: The court had banned the use of stone crushers during an earlier date. Ramnagar resident Anand Singh Negi had filed the PIL stating that Manral stone crusher is operating illegally in Sakkhanpur near Corbett National Park, "without PCB licence".

news.title: Chandigarh admin proposes fine of upto Rs 2 lakh for building misuse violations
news.para: The UT has recommended to increase the penalty from the current Rs 500 to Rs 2 lakh. Fine for each day, during which the offence is proved to have continued after the first day, was proposed to be increased from Rs 20 to Rs 8,000 per day.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body urges people to pay property tax online comfortably
news.para: ​​The officials claimed that in the financial year that ended MC received 30 percent tax returns through online mode as over 70000 returns came online but they want to touch at least 1 lakh mark. For this, they are planning to create public awareness.

news.title: Rajasthan: 48,000 incomplete PMAY-G homes in 10 districts to be inspected
news.para: Rural development and panchayati raj minister Ramesh Chand Meena on Friday gave directions to conduct a state-level inspection of 48,344 houses in 10 districts, the construction of which remained incomplete under the Pradhan Mantri Awaas Yojana-Grameen (PMAY-G) during the period 2016-17 to
